# Wine Spectator — Napa Valley Ultimate Guide
# Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, Mapbox GL

## Project purpose
Evergreen digital companion to Wine Spectator's annual Napa Valley print guide.
Extends editorial reach and supports pluggable sponsor/advertiser integrations.
Companion to the June 2026 print issue of Wine Spectator magazine.

## Brand & design
- Typography: Cormorant Garamond (display/headlines) + DM Sans (body/UI)
- Palette:
    --ink: #1A1612
    --cream: #F7F3EC
    --bordeaux: #6B1C2A
    --gold: #C4943A
    --sage: #5C6B52
    --dust: #E8E0D0
    --mist: #9B9283
- Tone: Editorial authority. Elevated but warm. Wine Spectator credibility meets modern travel UX.
- Motion: Framer Motion for page transitions and scroll reveals. Subtle, never showy.
- Reference aesthetic: Condé Nast Traveler meets wine authority. Think NYT Cooking meets Robb Report.
- NO purple gradients. NO generic SaaS aesthetics. NO Inter font. NO cookie-cutter layouts.

## Architecture rules
- App Router ONLY. Never use pages/ directory.
- All data lives in /src/data/ as typed TypeScript files.
- Sponsor slots driven entirely by /src/data/sponsors.ts — enable/disable per section without touching component code.
- Mapbox GL via react-map-gl. Use custom dark/terrain map style for Napa Valley.
- All winery/restaurant/hotel entries have:
    slug, name, coords [lng, lat], region, rating?, description, excerpt,
    sponsorTier (null | 'standard' | 'featured' | 'presenting'), images[]

## Sponsor integration model
- null        = organic editorial, no sponsor treatment
- 'standard'  = subtle badge + outbound link only
- 'featured'  = elevated card, custom content block, logo
- 'presenting' = full section takeover — hero banner, custom palette override, logo lockup
- sponsors.ts is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for all monetization. Never hardcode sponsor names in page/component files.

## Editorial sections (from June 2026 print issue)
- napaLede       → Opening feature / introduction
- napaLandmarks  → Landmark wineries of Napa
- napaJudgment   → Judgment of Paris legacy feature
- napaOakville   → Oakville AVA regional guide
- napaRutherford → Rutherford AVA regional guide
- napaCalistoga  → Calistoga AVA regional guide
- napaYountville → Yountville town guide
- napaPritchard  → Pritchard Hill AVA guide
- napaDT         → Downtown Napa guide
- napaTaco       → Dining / restaurant feature
- napaSTH        → Stay / hotels guide
- napaCalendar   → Events calendar

## Component conventions
- 'use client' ONLY when needed: maps, animations, interactive filters, forms
- Prefer server components for all editorial content pages
- Placeholder images: use /public/placeholders/ with aspect ratio wrapper divs
- Coords always [longitude, latitude] for Mapbox
- All article/winery/hotel data imported from /src/data/ — never inline in components
- Use Framer Motion variants for staggered list reveals and page transitions
- Section headings always use Cormorant Garamond italic for the decorative word

## File naming
- Components: PascalCase.tsx
- Data files: camelCase.ts
- Page routes: kebab-case directories

## Do not
- Do NOT use pages/ router
- Do NOT hardcode sponsor names or logos in components
- Do NOT use Tailwind default blue as any primary color — use CSS variables
- Do NOT use lorem ipsum — use contextual Napa Valley placeholder copy
- Do NOT use default Mapbox streets style — use terrain or custom dark style
- Do NOT fetch data client-side if it can be static/server-side
